File: Eben Etzebeth becomes the latest high-profile Springbok to join the Sharks. AFP/Filippo Monteforte DURBAN - The Sharks have added Eben Etzebeth to their star-studded squad. The World Cup-winning lock joins the Durban franchise from French club Toulon. READ: Springbok Etzebeth to exit Toulon for 'personal reasons' Etzebeth was one of the highest-paid rugby players in the world at a club that never shies away from splashing out on big signings. Now he'll be reunited with former Province teammates Siya Kolisi and Bongi Mbonambi at Kings Park.